700140f-a.title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Trinity Avenue
700140f-a.text:
East 149th Street (foreground), at the N.W. corner of Trinity Ave. The 2-story frame dwellings on the embankment, the rears of which are shown, face on an alley called Terrace Place, and are reached by a stairway directly beyond the garage on Trinity Ave.
June 21, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

700141f-a.title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Trinity Avenue
700141f-a.text:
East 149th Street, north side, east from Trinity Ave. to Concord
Ave.
June 21, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
